::: {.doc-subject}

Plot cumulative incidence functions from a fitted Aalen-Johansen estimator.
:::

::: {.doc-usage-source}
Usage

[Source](https://github.com/rich-iannone/greenwood/blob/main/greenwood/viz/_cif.py#L173-L365){target="_blank" rel="noopener"}
:::

::: {.doc-signature .doc-Kind.FUNCTION}
```python
viz.plot_cif(
    aj,
    *,
    conf_int=True,
    risk_table=False,
    times=None,
    title=None,
    xlab="Time",
    ylab="Cumulative incidence",
    width=400,
    height=300,
    backend="altair"
)
```
:::

::: {.doc-text}

Renders one cumulative incidence curve per competing cause as a right-continuous step function.
The chart is faceted by cause (one panel per event type). Stratified fits (produced by passing
`by=` to `AalenJohansen.fit()`) draw one colored line per group within each panel. An optional
shaded confidence band shows the point-wise uncertainty.
:::

## Parameters {.doc-parameters}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code>[aj]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [AalenJohansen]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   A fitted `AalenJohansen` object. Unstratified fits draw a single curve per panel. Stratified
    fits draw one colored curve per group.

<code>[conf_int]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [bool]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[True]{.va}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   If `True` (default), draw a shaded point-wise confidence band around each curve.

<code>[risk_table]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [bool]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[False]{.va}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   If `True`, stack an aligned numbers-at-risk table beneath the curves.

<code>[times]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [Any]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Query times for the numbers-at-risk table (used only when `risk_table=True`). Defaults to
    six evenly spaced times from `0` to the largest observed follow-up time.

<code>[title]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [str | None]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [None]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Optional overall plot title.

<code>[xlab]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [str]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[&quot;Time&quot;]{.st}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   X-axis label (default `"Time"`).

<code>[ylab]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [str]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[&quot;Cumulative incidence&quot;]{.st}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Y-axis label (default `"Cumulative incidence"`).

<code>[width]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [int]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[400]{.dv}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Width of each cause panel in pixels (default `400`).

<code>[height]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [int]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[300]{.dv}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Height of each cause panel in pixels (default `300`).

<code>[backend]{.doc-parameter-name}[:]{.doc-parameter-annotation-sep} [str]{.doc-parameter-annotation} [=]{.doc-parameter-default-sep .op} [[&quot;altair&quot;]{.st}]{.doc-parameter-default}</code>

:   Plotting backend. Currently only `"altair"` is supported.
:::

## Returns {.doc-returns}

::: {.doc-definition-items}
<code> [altair.Chart]{.doc-parameter-annotation}</code>

:   An interactive Altair chart. Each panel corresponds to one competing cause. Groups are
    distinguished by color.
:::

## Examples {.doc-examples}

Fit the Aalen-Johansen estimator on the bundled mgus2 dataset, where patients may progress to
malignancy (PCM) or die first:

::: {#c16c367c .cell execution_count=1}
``` {.python .cell-code}
import numpy as np
import greenwood as gw

# Load data and build a competing-risks response
mg = gw.load_dataset("mgus2", backend="polars")
etime = np.where(mg["pstat"] == 1, mg["ptime"], mg["futime"])
cause = np.where(mg["pstat"] == 1, 1, 2 * mg["death"])
y = gw.Surv.multistate(etime, event=cause, states=("pcm", "death"))

# Fit the Aalen-Johansen estimator and plot cumulative incidence
aj = gw.AalenJohansen().fit(y)
gw.plot_cif(aj)
```

